   {:e #blake3 "495bc53091a3066bb470660a40c77c725042d8a11751cc608e5fe946c544078f" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "What connects thinking about topology and coupling for ... to ADR-FOUNDATION-017: THE HYPOTHETICO-DEDUCTIVE LOOP. The complete ...?; Session entity: :recon/trace-f2345fdfacba761b; Session entity: :runtime/req-4be2df5ba65cee99; Session entity: :recon/trace-0395d1b7f4e92c40; Session entity: unnamed entity; Session entity: :recon/trace-8f3c75440a256458; What connects thinking about topology and coupling for ... to t-420f?; Session entity: :recon/trace-3d3bae6d1673fbf5; Session entity: :recon/trace-f36d001a75362c9e; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-sum-sq; What connects thinking about topology and coupling for ... to AUDIT ARCH-SOUNDNESS: Subsystem soundness classification — ...?; Session entity: :runtime/req-497713eaf6c0a79d; Session entity: :runtime/req-13fc252b5e172cf1; Session entity: :task/t-f79b9b03; Session entity: :task/t-bb5fd558; Session entity: :task/t-d0995596; Session entity: :config/concept-join-threshold; Session entity: :recon/trace-155549f3f857dfdb; Session entity: :config/concept-sigmoid-temperature; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-count; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-sum; Session entity: :runtime/req-e904324438fb016a\nC9-AGENT-IDENTITY-FINAL: Implementation spec for automatic per-process agent identity (C9-P4). PROBLEM: All observations from parallel subagents get the same AgentId because they all use the default --agent braid:user. The agreement detection correctly requires 2+ agents so returns empty. SOLUTION: Three-tier resolution in the observe command dispatch (mod.rs): (1) Explicit --agent flag overrides everything. (2) BRAID_AGENT env var for orchestrated subagents. (3) Auto-derived from PID: format braid:pid-{PID}. Unique per process, stable within session, zero ceremony. ALSO: Session auto-detect in main.rs:136-158 should use the same resolved agent ID when creating the session entity, so :session/agent matches the observation agent. WHERE: crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs observe dispatch (line ~2633), and other command dispatches that accept --agent. Also main.rs session auto-detect. SUBSTRATE-INDEPENDENT: No provider-specific logic. PID is universal. Env var is universal. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Two parallel braid observe from different PIDs produce different AgentIds. (B) Sequential commands from same PID produce same AgentId. (C) Explicit --agent overrides. (D) BRAID_AGENT env var overrides PID. (E) find_agreement_clusters returns non-empty when two PIDs observe same finding.; C9-OBSERVE-SUBCOMMANDS: Implementation spec for braid observe {list, search, show, recent} subcommands. GROUNDED IN CODEBASE: The exact pattern exists in crates/braid/src/commands/task.rs. task.rs has: all_tasks(store) at kernel level (task.rs), list() at CLI level (commands/task.rs:42), search() at CLI level (commands/task.rs:367), show() at CLI level (commands/task.rs:170). Each follows the same pattern: load store, call kernel function, filter/format, return CommandOutput. KERNEL SIDE (concept.rs or new observation.rs): New fn all_observations(store: &Store) -> Vec<ObservationSummary>. ObservationSummary struct: entity (EntityId), title (String, first 80 chars of body), body (String, full text), confidence (f64), category (Option<String>), concept_name (Option<String>, from :exploration/concept ref), timestamp (u64, from datom.tx.wall_time()), tags (Vec<String>). Implementation: iterate store.attribute_datoms(:exploration/body), for each Assert datom collect entity, extract body text, look up :exploration/confidence, :exploration/category, :exploration/concept via store.live_value(). Sort by timestamp descending. CLI SIDE (commands/observe.rs — extend existing file): Add subcommands to the existing Observe command. Currently braid observe TEXT creates an observation. Add: ObserveAction::List (list all, optional --concept filter), ObserveAction::Search { pattern } (substring match on body), ObserveAction::Show { id } (full entity detail), ObserveAction::Recent { limit } (most recent N, default 20). Each follows the exact task.rs pattern: call all_observations(), filter, format as human/agent/json/tsv output. CLAP STRUCTURE: braid observe is currently a positional TEXT argument. Change to subcommand-based: braid observe TEXT -c 0.9 (create, backward compat via default subcommand or positional), braid observe list, braid observe search PATTERN, braid observe show ENTITY, braid observe recent N. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid observe list shows all observations with confidence and truncated body. (B) braid observe search AUDIT returns the 226 audit observations. (C) braid observe show <entity> shows full body, confidence, category, concept, tags, timestamp. (D) braid observe recent 10 shows the 10 most recent. (E) All output modes work (human, agent, json, tsv). (F) Existing braid observe TEXT creation is not broken.; Session entity: :task/t-9821a10e; Session entity: :task/t-3115acf1; C9-TEST-FINAL: Comprehensive test plan for the complete C9 solution. Must verify BOTH paths (proactive seed + reactive observe subcommands) work end-to-end. UNIT TESTS (in kernel): Already have 19 tests for C9-P1/P2/P3/P5. Need: all_observations() tests (empty store, store with observations, correct field extraction, sorted by timestamp). UNIT TESTS (in CLI): observe list renders all observations. observe search filters correctly. observe show displays full entity. observe recent limits correctly. Creation still works (backward compat). INTEGRATION TEST (tests/c9_second_order.rs): Create store with observations from 3 agents (using different AgentIds in TxData). Run agreement detection — verify clusters form. Run seed assembly — verify convergent findings in orientation. Call all_observations — verify correct count and fields. E2E SCRIPT (scripts/e2e_c9_complete.sh): (1) braid init. (2) BRAID_AGENT=agent-1 braid observe 'F(S) stagnant at 0.62' -c 0.9. (3) BRAID_AGENT=agent-2 braid observe 'Fitness stuck at 0.62 for 13 sessions' -c 0.85. (4) BRAID_AGENT=agent-3 braid observe 'F(S) not moving verification needed' -c 0.9. (5) braid observe list — verify 3 observations shown. (6) braid observe search 'stagnant' — verify at least 1 match. (7) braid observe recent 2 — verify exactly 2 shown. (8) braid seed --task 'synthesize' — verify Convergent findings section present. (9) Assert all exit codes 0. DIAGNOSTIC LOGGING: Each E2E step logs command, output, and assertion result. On failure: dump store state (datom count, observation count, agent groups).; C9-COMPLETE-SOLUTION: The C9 EPIC must solve the COMPLETE problem, not just the seed path. The original problem: an agent with 226 audit observations could not synthesize them and fell back to reading markdown files. Two capabilities are needed, BOTH required, NEITHER sufficient alone: (1) PROACTIVE PATH (seed): When a session starts, the seed surfaces convergent findings automatically. This is C9-P1 through C9-P4 — MOSTLY DONE. The kernel primitives work, the seed rendering is in place, only agent identity (C9-P4) remains to activate it with real multi-agent data. (2) REACTIVE PATH (observe subcommands): Mid-session, the agent needs to search, list, show, and navigate observations. This is COMPLETELY MISSING. There is no braid observe list, no braid observe search, no braid observe show. The agent has braid task search but NO equivalent for observations. The evidence: in this session I successfully used braid task search AUDIT to find 102 audit tasks. If braid observe search AUDIT existed, I would have found the 226 observations without reading markdown. The API must mirror braid task exactly: braid observe list (all observations), braid observe search PATTERN (keyword search), braid observe show ENTITY (full detail), braid observe recent N (most recent). Same subcommand pattern, same output style, same composability. This is the unix answer — same verbs, different noun.; MEASUREMENT: braid status at 151K datoms = 3.2-3.9s (3 runs). Store growing ~35 datoms per status invocation from concurrent agents. 12,738 transaction files. Cache hit confirmed (store.bin exists and is fresh). The 3.3s is NOT the seal_existing_txns regression (already removed). This is the pre-existing O(N) datom scan pattern from audit findings PERF-002/PERF-005. The harvest command at 28.5s is the same root cause amplified (15+ full datom scans in the harvest pipeline).; C9-OPTION-ANALYSIS: Scoring 5 options for observation retrieval ergonomics. The test: can I answer 'what are the top audit findings?' in one command? OPTION A (braid recall): New command, context-aware, auto-groups by concept. Score: 8/10. Pro: purpose-built for the exact use case. Con: new command = new code surface, duplicates query logic, doesn't compose with existing commands. New concept to learn. OPTION B (improve braid seed): Make seed work mid-session with better observation surfacing. Score: 5/10. Pro: reuses existing infrastructure. Con: seed is designed for session-start budget-constrained injection, not mid-session exploration. Overloading its purpose violates single-responsibility. OPTION C (improve braid query): Add shorthand observation queries. Score: 6/10. Pro: extends existing query command, composable. Con: query is already complex (Datalog + entity + attribute modes), adding observation-specific shortcuts is a leaky abstraction. OPTION D (improve braid status --verbose): Score: 4/10. Status is a dashboard, not an exploration tool. Making it show 20 observation bodies makes it too long. Wrong tool for the job. OPTION E (add --list --search --show to braid observe): Score: 9/10. This is the unix answer. braid observe creates observations. braid observe --list shows them. braid observe --search 'AUDIT' finds them. braid observe --show <id> displays one. Exactly mirrors braid task {list,search,show}. Zero new concepts. Composes with existing patterns. The implementation is trivial: same pattern as task.rs search/list/show but over :exploration/body entities. Observation is already the noun. List/search/show are already the verbs the agent knows from task management. EVIDENCE: I already successfully used 'braid task search AUDIT' to find audit tasks. If 'braid observe --search AUDIT' existed, I would have used it to find observations instead of falling back to markdown files. The failure mode was: the search verb existed for tasks but not for observations. WINNER: Option E. Add --list, --search, --show to braid observe." :op :assert}
